names.details: Cezīre-i Cerbe: It is still an Islamic land. Conquered by Suleiman the Magnificent. It is in a narrow strait and Sicily is to its north. The island’s length is sixty miles, and the breadth of its eastern end is fifteen miles. It has Berber and Sammure tribes and various kinds of Franks. [translation]
